About
The filming location of the popular reality television show Pawn Stars attracts fans from all over the world and those looking to get their own items appraised. If you happen to swing by on a shoot day, you might be one of the lucky few cast as an extra on the show. In addition to antiques, collectibles, and jewelry, you’ll find a section of Pawn Stars memorabilia. You can visit Gold & Silver Pawn Shop as part of a reality show tour that takes you to various Vegas landmarks that have made it big on the small screen. – Tripadvisor

    Pretty cool famous location and TV Show.
    Stopped by on a weekday while in town. None of the cast was there. Souvenirs were available, pretty good size crowd, and just being there was cool. I planned on pawning some things just to have a memory and experience. Didn’t pawn anything. Interesting items on display. Worth a go if you like the show or Vegas attractions. Bought a shirt and took some pics.

  • Ray H

    Reality TV Las Vegas Pawn Shop Review
    The store was as I would have expected. It is a working Pawn Shop. There were several items from the show that had not sold yet and were really on the show. We expected that there would be souvenirs to buy, such as T-Shirts, etc. but did not really expect that there would be anything else we would be interested in buying at all, but were pleasantly surprised. We found one item that we liked. The price was near retail, but, when we asked a salesperson, we were able to negotiate a 25% discount. The item was very well wrapped up to avoid breakage. It is a fun place to visit.
    Visited October 2023

It’s a Pawn Shop
Jun 2024 • Couples
Funny to read the bad reviews here on TripAdvisor. It’s a pawn shop, nothing more. I’m a fan of the show and was drinking nearby at Dino’s Lounge so decided to take the 3 minute drive and visit. I saw a few cool items and the 100 oz. Hunt Brothers silver bar priced at $3,000 was actually a good deal considering silver trading at $31. Bought done tshirts, shot glasses and keychains as souvenirs as I didn’t feel like lugging a 100 oz silver bar across Vegas with me but I was tempted. Almost went to Ricks Rolling BBQ down the street but I was not hungry enough to justify. Enjoyed seeing the shop as a fan of the show. It’s mindless entertainment and somewhat educational if you like history.
